hopobject.body: How many would you like? pharmabuyotc.com The record gap between borrowing and lending rates and even the 3% difference between long and short gilt yields should be added to the bill for cleaning up the mess left by Fred Goodwin and co. Essentially, QE means the banks can borrow for nothing and lend at rates barely changed from the boom years â my credit card offers me cash at 27%. (By the way, these high rates cannot be explained away by default risk, because bad debts have barely increased in the last few years).
